==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Impetration
<hw>Im`pe*tra"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>impetratio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>imp⟦eacute⟧tration</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of impetrating, or obtaining by petition or
entreaty.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In way of <qex>impertation</qex> procuring the removal or
allevation of our crosses.</q> <rj><qau>Barrow.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Old Eng. Law)</fld> <def>The obtaining of benefice
from Rome by solicitation, which benefice belonged to the disposal of
the king or other lay patron of the realm.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Impetrative</ent>⟦br⟧
